ZCZC GE95
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
MONDAY TO THURSDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE MARITIME AND COASTGUARD AGENCY
AT 252300 UTC
A SLOW MOV HIGH PRESSURE SYSTEM 1040 CENTRED OVER SCOTLAND GRADUALLY
INTENSIFIES AND BECOMES 1043 BY THE AFTERNOON ON TUESDAY. THIS HIGH THEN
DRIFTS NWWARDS AND DECLINES TO 1030 BY 1800 UTC ON THURSDAY. STRG WINDS INITIALLY
IN WIGHT AND PORTLAND. THESE WILL GRADUALLY DECREASE FM THE E TURNING ISOL
ACROSS BOTH AREAS AND THEN WILL EASE BY TUESDAY MORNING. FURTHER STRG WINDS
WILL DEVELOP ACROSS THE ENGLISH CHANNEL AREAS ON WEDNESDAY MORNING MOV WWARDS
THROUGH THE CELTIC SEA AND EASING BY THE AFTERNOON. ELSEWHERE A SWATHE OF
STRGER WINDS GRADUALLY DEVELOPS FM THE NE IN THE N SEA WITH STRG WINDS FOR
A TIME WITHIN VIKING N UTSIRE S UTSIRE AND FORTIES DURING THE FIRST HALF
OF TUESDAY. THROUGHOUT THE SECOND HALF OF TUESDAY THESE WINDS WILL GRADUALLY
EASE CEASING BY WEDNESDAY MORNING WITH NO STRG WINDS DEVELOPING FOR A TIME.
ON THURSDAY MORNING FURTHER STRG WINDS WILL MOV SWWARDS INTO VIKING N UTSIRE
S UTSIRE AND FORTIES.
